			<gmd:abstract>
				<gco:CharacterString>
					The UK Air Quality Reanalysis (AQREAN) dataset, generated as part of the SPF Clean Air Programme, provides a high-resolution, long-term record of atmospheric composition across the United Kingdom and Republic of Ireland. Spanning a 17-year period from January 1, 2003, to December 31, 2019, the dataset offers gridded surface-level data at an hourly temporal resolution.

					The data is derived from the AQREAN model, a configuration based on the Met Office’s Air Quality in the Unified Model (AQUM). To ensure accuracy, a Statistical Post Processing of Observations (SPPO) method is applied to surface-level concentrations of key pollutants—including O3, NO, NO2, SO2, CO, PM2.5, and PM10—correcting model biases using actual ground-based observations from background monitoring sites.

					The dataset is provided at a horizontal resolution of 0.1 degree (approximately 10 km) in NetCDF format. In addition to primary pollutants, it includes a wide range of meteorological variables (such as wind speed, temperature, and precipitation), the Daily Air Quality Index (DAQI), and detailed particulate components like black carbon and sulphate. The latest Version 1.1 features an improved land-sea mask to ensure all land areas and small islands are represented, alongside corrections for missing timesteps and negative precipitation values.
					
					Full details about this dataset can be found at https://storymaps.arcgis.com/stories/bad1f0f37372421eb777e307b71a28cd
				</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:abstract>
			<gmd:purpose>
				<gco:CharacterString>Datasets generated by the Met Office to provide a representation of past pollutant concentrations across the UK.</gco:CharacterString>
			</gmd:purpose>
